{"questionId":"27199","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A cafe makes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> litres of coffee each morning. The cafe’s profit each morning, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math>, measured in dollars, is modelled by the following equation</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>100</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> is a positive constant.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the maximum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>. Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math> is a constant.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equating their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> to zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>1000</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>100</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> back into given expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>10</mn><mi>k</mi></mrow><mn>30</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>300</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mn>900</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mtext>max</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow><mn>9</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>222</mn><mo>…</mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27199","referenceCode":"22M.2.SL.TZ2.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the maximum value of C in terms of k. Give your answer in the form pk3, where p is a constant.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}